    "narrative": "The Austin Waves open today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our premier offensive catalyst. With an elite score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a high-leverage matchup against Teng, bolstered by a significant 16% park adjustment and an aggressive lead-off slot that projects for high run-scoring potential. Supporting him are **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (73.86) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (72.97); the latter is an excellent play today due to a favorable platoon advantage against Holmes, C, which offsets the inherent risks of a pitcher capable of suppressing base-stealing opportunities. While **Kyle Tucker** faces a respectable matchup against Janson Junk, his 69.35 score remains a high-floor anchor for the lineup, though he is currently overshadowed by the ceiling of our top-tier trio.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved the benching of **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the cut with a score of 52.47. Despite a favorable batting order spot, the optimizer favored the higher output of **Andy Pages** (56.37) and **Dominic Smith** (47.87), whose platoon-adjusted profiles against their respective matchups provided more cumulative efficiency for our 5x5 targets. The primary risk to monitor today is the uncertainty surrounding **Liam Hicks**; his 40.40 score is fragile, hovering near our \u201cbelow floor\u201d threshold. Facing an elite arm in Ohtani, **Liam Hicks** is the most likely candidate to underperform his projection, and we will be monitoring the official lineup confirmation closely to ensure no further downgrades occur. We have opted to keep **Nasim Nunez** on the bench despite his latent value in our scarcest category (SB) because he is projected to hit at the bottom of the order against a tough defensive catcher/pitcher battery, which significantly hampers his utility today.",
